import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import networkx as nx

# Create a directed graph
G = nx.DiGraph()

# Define nodes
nodes = {
    "Start": "Neuron Receives a Task",
    "Autonomous": "Can the neuron execute autonomously?",
    "Execute": "Neuron executes task and optimizes",
    "Validation": "Does the neuron require validation?",
    "Request Approval": "Neuron requests validation from the Nucleus or human participant",
    "Approved": "Task validated and executed",
    "Denied": "Request denied, neuron adjusts or aborts",
    "Emergency": "Does this pose an ethical or security risk?",
    "Intervention": "Nucleus intervenes and adjusts protocols",
}

# Add nodes to the graph
for key, value in nodes.items():
    G.add_node(value)

# Define edges
edges = [
    ("Neuron Receives a Task", "Can the neuron execute autonomously?"),
    ("Can the neuron execute autonomously?", "Neuron executes task and optimizes"),
    ("Can the neuron execute autonomously?", "Does the neuron require validation?"),
    ("Does the neuron require validation?", "Neuron requests validation from the Nucleus or human participant"),
    ("Neuron requests validation from the Nucleus or human participant", "Task validated and executed"),
    ("Neuron requests validation from the Nucleus or human participant", "Request denied, neuron adjusts or aborts"),
    ("Task validated and executed", "Neuron executes task and optimizes"),
    ("Request denied, neuron adjusts or aborts", "Neuron executes task and optimizes"),
    ("Neuron executes task and optimizes", "Does this pose an ethical or security risk?"),
    ("Does this pose an ethical or security risk?", "Nucleus intervenes and adjusts protocols"),
    ("Does this pose an ethical or security risk?", "Neuron executes task and optimizes"),
]

# Add edges to the graph
G.add_edges_from(edges)

# Draw the graph
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
pos = nx.spring_layout(G, seed=42)
nx.draw(G, pos, with_labels=True, node_color="lightblue", edge_color="gray", node_size=3000, font_size=8, font_weight="bold", arrows=True)

# Show plot
plt.title("Mycelium Intelligence - Neuron Decision Tree")
plt.show()
